
"HelloSignal" is another small Qt4-based project to create the shared library to be loaded into the
existing ROOT session

   The shared library contains the Qt UI created with the Qt4 designer and
RootCint dictionary to communicate with the UI from the ROOT macro/command
prompt.

To  build and run the  application do

   1. "Un-tar" the archive
       tar -xzvf HelloSignal.tar.gz

   2  Invoke:

      qmake
      make

   3. Usage:
      3.1. start root session
      3.2. Load the libHelloSignal.so shared library

   4. To change the GUI invoke the Qt4 designer:


